## Workflow

This project uses the [flow plugin](https://github.com/by-dev-tools/flow) for its 11-step managed-autonomy loop. See `core-docs/workflow.md` (project overlay, if any) and `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/docs/workflow.md` (canonical) for the loop itself. Run `/flow:workflow-help` for an in-session reminder.

Project-specific configuration lives in [`flow.config.json`](./flow.config.json) at the repo root.

## Docs

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `core-docs/spec.md` | Product vision, problem, solution, feature table, open questions |
| `core-docs/plan.md` | Current focus, active work items, handoff notes |
| `core-docs/roadmap.md` | Horizons (Now / Next / Later) + § Exploration |
| `core-docs/history.md` | Per-PR decision log: what + why + tradeoffs |
| `core-docs/feedback.md` | User feedback synthesized to rules (FB-XXXX) |
| `core-docs/design-language.md` | (UI projects) Tokens, axioms, components, motion — read before any UI change |

## Rules (auto-loading)

| Rule | Loads on | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `.claude/rules/safety.md` | safety-critical paths ({{SAFETY_PATHS}}) | Read recent git log before modifying; never silently downgrade error handling |
| `.claude/rules/ui.md` (UI projects) | UI file edits | Read design-language.md first; use tokens, not raw values |

Plugin-shipped rules (general workflow discipline, plan format, doc format, exploration triggers) load automatically when the flow plugin is installed. See `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/rules/` for the full set.

## Quality bar

- **Polished over partial.** Every visible control does its job. Wire-vs-defer: if the gap is < 1 day, wire it; else remove the visible affordance and capture in roadmap.
- **Scope expansion is additive.** Ship the smallest polished form first.
- **No false affordances.** A button that doesn't work is a bug equivalent to a crash.

